	<Title>
		Want to lose weight? Eat more fiber
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;High-fiber foods generally take longer to chew. This gives your body time to register when you&apos;re no longer hungry, so you&apos;re less likely to overeat. And high-fiber foods tend to make you feel full longer, so you won&apos;t be as ravenous later. Finally, high-fiber foods tend to have fewer calories for the same volume of food. Choose whole grains and whole-grain products, fruits and vegetables, and beans, peas and other legumes.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
